      <section class="why-section" id="why">
        <div class="container">
          <p class="section-label reveal">Why llmrouter</p>
          <h2 class="section-heading reveal">
            Four properties. That&rsquo;s the whole pitch.
          </h2>
          <p class="section-sub reveal">
            Most multi-LLM libraries reach for breadth. llmrouter is
            narrower and more opinionated &mdash; designed around the
            shape of code that has to ship to production.
          </p>
          <div class="pillars reveal">
            <article class="pillar">
              <div class="pillar-icon">S</div>
              <h3>Streaming-first</h3>
              <p>
                Channel-based deltas with a producer goroutine and
                proper <code>context.Context</code> cancellation that
                propagates all the way to the in-flight HTTP request.
                Cancel the context and the upstream connection closes
                &mdash; no leaked goroutines, no orphaned token spend.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="pillar">
              <div class="pillar-icon">B</div>
              <h3>Byte passthrough</h3>
              <p>
                Every chunk preserves its original wire bytes via
                <code>Chunk.Raw</code>. Build proxies and gateways
                that are byte-identical to upstream OpenAI without
                re-marshalling typed structs &mdash; the bytes you
                forward downstream are the bytes you received.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="pillar">
              <div class="pillar-icon">A+E</div>
              <h3>Audio + embeddings</h3>
              <p>
                Chat is not the whole story. v0.3 adds
                <code>Speaker</code> (TTS), <code>Transcriber</code>
                (STT), and <code>Embedder</code> &mdash; same
                streaming and cancellation semantics, backed by
                OpenAI, ElevenLabs, Cartesia, Deepgram, Voyage, and
                more.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="pillar">
              <div class="pillar-icon">D</div>
              <h3>Boring dependencies</h3>
              <p>
                The only dependencies are the Go standard library,
                <code>google/uuid</code>, and the official vendor SDKs
                for the cloud providers (AWS, Google, Anthropic). No
                surprise transitive trees.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
          <div class="why-cta reveal">
            <strong>llmrouter</strong> is the library a gateway is
            built on top of &mdash; not the gateway itself.
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="features" id="features">
        <div class="container">
